		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b>Follow-ups</b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>95/09-Follow-Ups</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						September 1995
Worth magazine/Departments<p>FOLLOW-UPS<p>* A federal grand jury in Newark, New Jersey, indicted talk show host Sonny Bloch in May on charges that he used his broadcasts to promote fraudulent investment schemes ("Sonny Bloch Faces the Music," June). In July, a grand jury in New York City handed down a second set of indictments__this time for eight counts of tax fraud, perjury, and obstruction of justice. Bloch also faces civil charges brought in Federal District Court in Manhattan by the Securities and Exchange Commission.<p>* Dr. Bernardo Nadal-Ginard, the cardiologist accused of defrauding the charitable foundation he ran at Children's Hospital in Boston ("Irreversible Damage," April), was sentenced on June 6 to one year in prison by a Suffolk Superior Court judge in Massachusetts. The sentencing followed Nadal-Ginard's conviction on 12 counts of larceny. He is currently free on appeal.<p><p>
KEYWORDS: Ethical Investing

					</font>
