<html>
	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 96/05-Hulbert's Heroes</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6007.html?worth+PCFN25.gif+Archives>
<img src="/ads/PCFN25.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>96/05-Hulbert's Heroes</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						For investment newsletters, the annual performance rankings from Hulbert Financial Digest are the Grammys, Oscars, and Emmys all rolled into one. Editor Mark Hulbert takes pains to point out that one-year performance is an unreliable predictor of long-term results. For example, this year's top newsletter, Medical Technology Stock Letter, was a big loser in 1994. But the winners of 1995 also include a number of long-term top performers. Among the more venerable are California Technology Stock Letter, which owns a spot among the top-five-performing newsletters for the past ten years, according to Hulbert, and The Prudent Speculator, The Oberweis Report, and OTC Insight, which have beaten the herd over the past eight years.  <p>  <p>
KEYWORDS: Mutual Funds Investing Strategies

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
	<a href="/index.html">
	<IMG SRC="/imgs/datalineyellow.gif" border=0 alt="Worth"></a><p>
</center>
<pre>


</pre>
					<tt><font size=+1>
					<center>
						<img src="/imgs/1page.gif"><br>About 1 page

					</font>
					</tt>
					</center>

					<pre>
					</pre>


					</font>
					<p>

