	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>96/09-Tips</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						
TeleBank, the new name for Arlington, Virginia's 60-year-old Metropolitan Bank, has become the first totally branchless bank doing business nationwide. Customers perform all transactions by phone, working with live representatives who are on call from 8 a.m. to 8 p.m. TeleBank uses some of the savings from eliminating brick and mortar and tellers to pay higher yields on CDs and money-market accounts: The rate as of June 27 on TeleBank's money-market account (4.93 percent for balances above $2,500) was almost twice the national average. And one-year CD rates (5.59 percent) were about 70 basis points better than average. Accounts are FDIC insured up to $100,000 and include ATM cards, but check-writing privileges are limited to three free checks a month (800-638-2265).<p>ADVICE ON THE CHEAP 
The Vanguard Group is now applying the low-cost philosophy behind its mutual funds to investment advice (800-523-1154). For $500, clients can have an in-house specialist (with certification as a chartered financial planner or the equivalent) do a onetime assessment of their finances and recommend one of seven asset-allocation models as well as suggest which funds to buy. T. Rowe Price has plans to start a similar program in 1997 for clients with at least $100,000 to invest.<p>FINANCIAL JOTTINGS
The PSE Tech 100 Index Portfolio Fund, launched in June by Principal Preservation (West Bend, Wisconsin), tracks the Pacific Stock Exchange technology index with price-weighted exposure to 100 companies. One catch: a 4.5 percent sales charge (800-826-4600).... Brian Kelly, former manager of Invesco's highly regarded Balanced Fund, has moved to Founders to run its Balanced and Blue Chip Funds (800-525-2440).... Mortgage REITs outperformed the Standard & Poor's 500 Stock Index in May with a total return of 6.53 percent versus 2.58 percent.<p><p><p>
KEYWORDS: Banking Industry, Mutual Funds Investing, Real Estate Investing

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
