		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>96/08-Briefs</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						Board Boondoggle?
A study by investment adviser Kinder, Lydenberg, Domini & Co. (617-547-7479) lists the amounts companies pay independent board members. Topping the list of 647 companies: <a name="NYSE:UNH"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=15007"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>United HealthCare</b></a>, with 1994 awards totaling $954,000, <a name="NYSE:SGI"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=11735"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Silicon Graphics</b></a> ($331,000), and <a name="NYSE:AIG"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=10095"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>American International Group</b></a> ($309,000). "It borders on incredible that you would have an independent board with compensation at that level," says author Peter Kinder. Investors who call can get the scoop on the top ten companies.<p>Ready Research 
Fidelity Investments' new RealTime Research (800-544-3198) service provides earnings projections, analyst recommendations, fund profiles, industry analyses, and market forecasts via the Internet for brokerage-account holders. Investors can also set up an option to alert them to news items or changes in recommendations on specific securities by fax or mail. Fidelity will waive the five-dollar monthly fee for the first three months for investors who sign up by August 31, and for investors with $50,000 in individual Fidelity accounts.<p>Financial Jottings
John Bogle Jr., 36-year-old son of Vanguard Group chairman John Bogle, has moved his stock-picking prowess from the Quantitative Group of Funds to his own fund family at Numeric Investors (800-NUMERIC).... Vanguard's Total International Portfolio (800-276-7235) index fund provides exposure to overseas markets for only 0.38 percent in fees, versus 1.82 percent for the average international equity fund.... Discount brokerage Jack White & Co. (800-233-3411) rolls out a money-market account in September that offers up to 20 percent off purchases from retailers.... Fidelity Investments will launch a FundsNet program that will let employers who use the firm to administer 401(k) plans choose from over 55 non-Fidelity funds, including offerings from Founders, PBHG, and USAA.<p><p><p>
KEYWORDS: Mutual Funds Investing

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
