		<title> Worth OnLine - 96/05-Prepare for Medicare</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6015.html?worth+PCFN16.gif+Archives>
<img src="/ads/PCFN16.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b>Prepare for Medicare</b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>96/05-Prepare for Medicare</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						May 1996 <p>Worth magazine/Personal Adviser  <p> PREPARE FOR MEDICARE <p>The window of opportunity for the best premiums closes quickly <p> By Morey Stettner  <p> If you or a parent is approaching age 65, it's not too soon to look into Medicare and Medigap policies for health insurance. And before long, it may be too late. Medicare premiums are lowest if you enroll three months before to four months after your 65th birthday; after that, the premiums may grow by 10 percent for each year you wait. At the same time, start comparing Medigap policies. These Medicare supplements, sold by private insurers, reimburse policyholders for costs not covered by Medicare, such as prescription drugs. Federal law guarantees that during the six months following enrollment in Medicare Part B (in which97 percent of Americans over 65 are enrolled) anyone can buy a Medigap policy regardless of health problems. After this six-month window, insurers are likely to require a medical screening, and applications can be denied.  <p> There are ten Medigap plans to choose from, labeled A through J; the benefits improve as you go down the alphabet. "The rates vary, so compare a few quotes from private insurers," says Sam Beller, president of Diversified Programs, a New York City insurance agency. "Also, check if you can get retiree health insurance from your former employer."  <p> The Social Security Administration offers a free booklet, 1996 Guide to Health Insurance for People With Medicare, with a directory of agencies providing free counseling on Medicare and Medigap coverage (800-772-1213). The Health Insurance Association of America offers free guides on Medigap and long-term-care policies:write to HIAA, Publication Office, 555 13th St., NW, Suite 600-E,Washington, D.C., 20004.   <p><p>
KEYWORDS: Health Insurance Industry, Government 

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
	<a href="/index.html">
	<IMG SRC="/imgs/datalineyellow.gif" border=0 alt="Worth"></a><p>
</center>
<pre>


</pre>
					<tt><font size=+1>
					<center>
						<img src="/imgs/2pages.gif"><br>About 2 pages

