<html>
  <head>
    <title>Indexing</title>
  </head>
  <body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000">
<table cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5 width=550>
<tr>
	<td width=390>
 <a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6007.html?worth+PCFN25.gif+Message%20Boards>
<img src="/ads/PCFN25.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>

	</td>
	<td width=150 valign=top> </td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width=390 valign=top>
<center>
<p>
<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b><p>
<pre>
</pre>
</center>
<blockquote>
    <center>
      <h1>Indexing</h1>
    </center>
<hr width=75%>
<center>[ <a href="http://www.worth.com/forums/talkfunds/ifunds/worthboard.html">Return to the Front of this Board</a> ]</center>
<p>Message Posted by <p><a href="mailto:Brooklynboy@juno.com">BrooklynBoy</a> on January 09, 1997 at 16:37:49:<p>
It appears to me that so much time is <br>invested to research out good stocks, <br>top mutual funds, etc. that for the <br>average person not familiar with <br>technical analysis why waste all that <br>time when you can buy mutual funds that <br>mirror most of the major market indexes. <br> So many studies have been done on <br>indexing that prove their value as an <br>investment. Now there won't be any high <br>flyers but I want to sleep at night and <br>get comfort in the effienciey of the <br>overall market.  Most index funds come <br>without sale charges and their annual <br>expenses tend to be amoung the lowest in <br>the industry.  Index funds typically <br>out-perform a large percentage of the <br>actively managed funds.  It seems like a <br>no brainer.<br>You can start with a S&P500 index(or a <br>50/50 combination of a growth and value <br>index funds).  You can add a small <br>cap and an international index fund.  <br>As time goes on the indexing concept <br>will most likely lead to a myriad of <br>investment options as fund companies <br>develop more and more index funds.<br>
<br>
<p><hr width=75%>
<center>[ <a href="http://www.worth.com/forums/talkfunds/ifunds/worthboard.html">Return to the Front of this Board</a> ]</center>
</blockquote>
</td><td width=150 valign=top>
<center><img src="/imgs/messageyellow.gif"></center>	</td>
